post_text:
Dear Kanab Middle School Parents,

Yesterday was a terrific first day of school! It was refreshing to have students back in the building!

For your information, we have a paraprofessional aide job position open. KMS is a great place to work! If you are interested, please apply at https://ksdstaff.sedck12.org/ksd/ap/job-detail-view.php?jid=74
The closing date is Aug 21.

Also we are still looking for one more parent Community Council member. Please fill out the attached form and return it to Mr. Bateman. No experience is needed as training will be provided. Be a decision maker for our school. Come join!

Lastly, school pictures are scheduled for next week on Aug 25. Our Back to School night will be different this year due to Covid. Each teacher will be recording a short introduction video presentation to send out instead of meeting in person. We will also have some information about logging into Canvas/SIS. Stay tuned!

Thanks and Go Regulators!

post_text:
Last night the Kane School Board approved the Kane District School Reopening Plan. Please review the guidelines and requirements for the upcoming school year.

Kane District will provide all students with 2 washable fabric masks, but students are welcome to wear any face covering that follows the State Public Health frequently asked questions:

Face covering means a cloth mask or plastic face shield that covers both the nose and mouth. A cloth face covering is secured to the head with ties, straps, or loops over the ears, or is wrapped around the lower face. A cloth face covering can be made of synthetic or natural fabrics.

Let's have a great year!

post_text:
Would you like to be a Substitute Teacher?

If you would like to be on the substitute teacher list at Kane School District for the 2020-21 school year, please follow this procedure:
1. Submit a job application to a principal at a school you would like to sub at.
2. Once you are recommended to sub by the principal, we will email you a link that you can use to access the required online district training (SafeSchools).
3. Pass background check. Fingerprinting can be done at the district office ($45 fee).
Contact Kim Blake at blakek@kane.k12.ut.us with questions you may have.
Those on the list from last year: please let Kim know if you would like to be on the list this year. We will email you the online training for this year. Thank you!

To apply, go to: https://kanek12.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Substitute-Application-2019.pdf

New KES Site Selection Information:

We have received requests from the public regarding the DRAFT proposal of the new elementary school at the downtown site and Ranchos location. In an effort to be transparent to the public, the Kane County School Board has made them available to the public. If you would like to comment on the site or building design, please email your comments to: https://kanek12.org/district/board-of-education/ Please know that the plans are in draft form in concept relating to space and possible placement of the new elementary school.

--

Ben Dalton, Ed.D.

Superintendent

HIRING BUS DRIVERS

KANE SCHOOL DISTRICT is accepting applications for part time route bus drivers. Split shift- morning & afternoon routes. Drivers needed at Valley schools. Applicants must be at least 21 yrs. of age, must be able to get a DOT health card and obtain a CDL driver license (district pays for endorsement training), must pass drug test, must pay for and pass a background check. Apply online via Applicant Portal. Closing date June 30, 2020 or until filled.

For job information and to apply online via Applicant Portal, go to: https://ksdstaff.sedck12.org/ksd/ap/applicant/login.php

post_text:
Kane District Job Opening - Seasonal Yard Work/Maintenance.

Full time/40 hrs-week, May - August. Under the direction of the Principal and/or Head Custodian, this position includes mowing lawns on commercial lawn mower, fixing and adjusting Rainbird sprinklers, fixing sprinkler valves, adjusting watering schedules, fertilizing and spraying weeds. May also include helping with other jobs inside and outside schools. Assisting in maintenance activities and performing other related duties as assigned. Regular attendance and timeliness is an essential job function to perform the duties and responsibilities of the position. Hourly pay depends on experience. If hired, a background check will be required ($45 fee). Must have a valid Utah driver license.
For job information and to apply online via Applicant Portal, go to Kane District website: www.kane.k12.ut.us, Under District dropdown, select Employment, scroll down to Applicant Portal links. Click on Job Search tab to see available jobs (not necessary to create an account to view available openings).

post_text:
Spring Sports Suspension Extended

MIDVALE, Utah (March 24, 2020) - The Utah High School Activities Association is announcing an extension to the ongoing suspension of the Association’s spring activities and athletics, due to ongoing statewide prevention efforts with the COVID-19 virus.

As a result of Governor Herbert’s directive in a March 23 press conference, the Association continues to suspend all UHSAA spring activities and athletics, including practice and/or team gatherings, until at least May 1, in line with the state-recommended extension to the school soft closure.

In consultation with board directives and information provided by state public health officials, the UHSAA has suspended spring activities and athletics, including practice and team gatherings, to properly fulfill best practices regarding protection of students and the general public. More information will be sent to member schools and/or districts as it becomes available.

--
Jon Oglesby, MPC
Assistant Director - Utah High School Activities Association

post_text:
Dixie State University
Emergency Response Plan for Concurrent Enrollment

Concurrent Enrollment classes taught on the high school campuses will follow the instructional directions set forth by their school district. At this time we anticipate this to mean courses will be taught virtually (online) upon returning from spring break.

Concurrent Enrollment classes taught on the university campus, or DSU Extension Centers, will follow DSU instructional protocols for full time students. Lecture courses will be taught virtually through Canvas as well as other electronic means, for the remainder of the semester. Classes that require hands-on experiences such as clinicals, labs and internships for completion will be addressed via the student’s instructor.

CNA courses for example, will complete lecture days electronically, but meet together for skills classes on their respective DSU campus.

Questions and concerns can be directed to DSU’s Concurrent Enrollment Department https://concurrent.dixie.edu/ (we suggest by e-mail).

post_text:
Coronavirus Information

We received the attached letter from the Utah Department of Health addressing concerns and giving information about the coronavirus. They have requested we share this letter with our staff and with each of you. Be sure to review this letter as it provides great information.

As the immediate health risk to the general is public is considered low, please remember part of good respiratory hygiene is staying home from school and events when sick. Don't forget to call the school office to excuse absences. Also, good hygiene among everyone who enters our school buildings is very important. These include regular hand washing and covering coughs and sneezes with a tissue or an elbow.

Hopefully with everyone's help we can stay healthy as a school.

post_text:
Kane School District: Attention Child Find
In accordance with Part B requirements of the Individuals with Disabilities Education Act 04 and with the Utah State Board of Education Special Education Rules, Kane County School District offers free assessments and evaluation for children, aged birth through 21, who parents, teachers, or others suspected of having a disability.
Kane School District is committed to ensuring that those students are identified, located, and evaluated, regardless of the severity of the disability, to identify if the student is in need of special education and related services. This child find requirement and practice also applies to those students enrolled in private schools.
If you suspect that a child who is not receiving special education services is in need of an evaluation to determine if that need exists, please contact Chris Kupfer, Kane District Special Education Director at 435-590-8144 or the special education teacher at your neighborhood school.

Constructions Bids Accepted

Kane County School District is accepting bids from qualified, licensed contractors for construction of a restroom/concession/storage building at the Kanab High School Baseball facility. This facility will be approximately 988 square feet and will be cinder block construction. Contractors desiring to bid on this project, please contact Quade Johnson to obtain a bid package. Sealed bids will be received at the Kane School District Office, 746 S 175 E, Kanab, UT 84741 (attn: Cary Reese) until 3:00 PM on Oct 24, 2019. Bids will be opened and reviewed at 9:00 AM on Oct 28, 2019 at the Kane School District Office. Construction work to commence no later than Nov 1, 2019, with final completion no later than Feb 29, 2020. Please contact Quade Johnson at johnsonq@kanek12.org with any questions. Kane School District reserves the right to reject any or all bids.

post_text:
Dear Kanab Middle School Parents,

We are excited to start school on Tuesday, August 13 and look forward to having students back! Just a reminder, the first day for Kanab Middle and High will be a full day. Kanab Middle School will end the day at 3:00pm. Kanab Elementary will be half day dismissing at 12:50.

Also, be sure to mark your calendars for our Back to School Night next Tuesday on August 20 at 6pm. We plan to have hot dogs and chips for those who attend so come and enjoy and bring an appetite! Back to School night will be a little different this year as parents and students will be able to visit each class hearing a brief overview of the upcoming year. We will start at 6 pm sharp by meeting in the gym/commons area for 10 minutes, and then off we go to the different classes with a three minute passing period.

Again we are excited to be back and hope to see you at our Back to School Night!

Go Regulators!

Also, be sure to mark your calendars for our Back to School Night next Tuesday on August 20 at 6pm. We plan to have hot dogs and chips for those who attend so come and enjoy and bring an appetite! Back to School night will be a little different this year as parents and students will be able to visit each class hearing a brief overview of the upcoming year. Must be willing to complete pertinent USBE trainings, which may require overnight travel. Understanding of andragogy and experience working with adults preferred. ESL training, strong math, reading, and communication skills preferred.

Kanab High School is hiring a
School Secretary/Bookkeeper

11 Month position (Aug-June), 40 hours per week, schedule follows school calendar.
Starting Date: August 1, 2019, but must be available for some training time during the summer. $15.58 per hour with benefits.
Applicant must be proficient in QuickBooks, Excel and Word. Must have experience with email, invoices, preparing deposits and cash boxes, reconciling bank statements, taxes, computers and the internet. Must have the ability to work with high school age students, parents and staff. Must be a self-starter with a positive attitude.
Must pay for and pass a background check. Open until June 17, 2019.

post_text: At last night's board meeting the Kane School Board honored this year's Sterling Scholars. Winners received $1000 scholarship, Runners Up received $500, and all others received $100. We appreciate all their hard work in their pursuit of excellence in scholarship, leadership and citizenship in the State of Utah. Well done, students! Winners: Nellie Bowman and Jamie Keller. Runners Up: Dylan Bistline, Lance Little and Morgan Stewart. Other Sterling Scholars: Kelsie Barrick, Logan Dean, Rebekah Esplin, Mackenzie Morgan, Ashlynn Spencer, Orrin Wood, Dustin Bistline, Ally Haycock, Alix Nokes and Emilie Oblad. Thanks and appreciation also goes out to the Sterling Scholar school advisors: Principal Jim Wood and Wanda Heaton from VHS, and Jennifer Yates and Kim Titus from KHS.

post_text:
CAREER DAY

Thursday April 4
We will be holding a Career Day for high school students in our district. There will be over 30 presenters from local businesses and entities here to share information about employment opportunities. This is an exciting event and a great chance to learn about the careers and jobs available in our area. We appreciate the sponsors and the work that has gone into creating this experience for our students.

We will hold shortened classes in the morning and at 11:45 we will have a free pizza lunch to kick off the event. Students will be able to attend 4 presentations and visit over 35 information tables on local employment. Attendees can apply for summer employment and sign up for interviews.

As this is a part of our school day, all students are expected to attend and attendance points will be awarded. The students' career fair will start at 11:45 and end at 2:55. Adults are invited to attend from 3 pm to 6 pm. If you have questions please contact Kanab High School at 644-5821. Thank you.

Roofing Bids Requested

Kane County School District is requesting re-roofing bids for the shingle section on the Valley High School building in Orderville, Utah.

Tear-off and dispose of all roofing materials, flashings and drip edge detail. Re-roof (shingles) approximately 24,000 square feet. Contractors responsible for their own measurements. There will be some deteriorated plywood deck replacement.

Mandatory bid walk will be April 16, 2019, at 1:00 PM at Valley High School, located at 150 North Center Street in Orderville, UT. Bid documents and details will be available at the bid walk. Contractor measurements can be taken at that time. Work can begin on May 27, and must be completed no later than June 30, 2019. For Questions, contact Cary Reese at 435-644-2555 ext. 2

post_text:
Walk More in Four!
Walking and biking challenge for students K-8 across the state, begins April 8 and runs through May 3. Participating students will be entered to win bikes, scooters, helmets and more from our prize pool worth $3,000. The more students walk or bike to school, the greater their chance of winning.

Walk or bike to school. Each time you walk or bike to school you’ll be entered for an additional chance to win a sweet prize.

Download the chart on http://saferoutes.utah.gov/walkmore/ to keep track of the days you walk or bike to school.

Submit your progress chart online as early as May 3 and no later than May 8.
Winners will be notified by phone or email. Winners will also be announced on the Safe Routes Utah Facebook page and website. Prizes will be distributed May 13-17.

SUBMISSIONS ARE ONLY ACCEPTED ONLINE. PLEASE USE THE FORM PROVIDED ON http://saferoutes.utah.gov/walkmore/

*Students are only eligible to win one prize.

Assignments to include Biology/Agricultural Biology, Natural Resource Science & Medical Anatomy & Physiology. Applicants must hold a current secondary Utah teaching certificate with Biological Science endorsement. shared_text:
Kane County School District
February 20, 2019 at 9:21 PM ·

Dear Students, Staff, and Patrons,

We want you to know that we are monitoring the weather closely this evening. The District will have spotters out early in the morning to determine if roads and schools will be ready for buses and patrons. Any decision for a delayed start or closing of schools occurs in the early morning hours when snowplows are out clearing school parking lots.

If a closure or delayed start occurs, the district will announce it here on the Kane District Facebook page and via email and phone calls from your building administrator through the school’s Parent Link notification system.
The announcement will be posted at approximately 6:00 am.

If no announcements are made by the district, school will proceed at the normally scheduled times.

As weather conditions may differ between neighborhoods, we honor a parent’s decision to have your child arrive late or stay home. Teachers will help students make up any work that students miss.

The announcement will be posted at approximately 6:00 am.

If no announcements are made by the district, school will proceed at the normally scheduled times.

As weather conditions may differ between neighborhoods, we honor a parent’s decision to have your child arrive late or stay home. Teachers will help students make up any work that students miss.

Kanab High School – Biology Teacher

Kanab High School is accepting applications for a full-time secondary teacher for 2019-2020 school year. Assignments to include Biology/Agricultural Biology, Natural Resource Science & Medical Anatomy & Physiology. Applicants must hold a current secondary Utah teaching certificate with Biological Science endorsement. Endorsements in MAPS, Natural Resource Management and Ag Science also encouraged, or are willing to work toward needed endorsements. Position may also require extracurricular duties as coach or advisor, as assigned by the principal.Salary based on Kane District salary schedule with full benefits. For more information and to apply online, go to Kane District website: http://www.kane.k12.ut.us/index.php/district/employment-opportunities
Closing date is May 1, 2019.

post_text:
Congratulations to KHS Larriettes!
First time ever 2A State Drill Team Champions!
The Lariettes also captured the 2A Academic All-State team title, with their 19 team members having a collective grade-point average of 3.77 out of a possible 4.0.
Way to work hard and represent Kane School District!
We are so proud of you!

“They danced with their hearts,” Coach Shellie Stewart said. “They left everything out on the floor. We were happy. We were winners before they announced the results.”

She hopes her dancers take more than the memory of winning a title.

“I hope they remember that they worked for something,” she said. “And, if they put their whole souls into it, anything is possible. It’s amazing. It’s surreal.”

This info is straight from Southwest Utah Health Department this morning:

The Southwest Utah Public Health Department is monitoring a case of mumps (a contagious viral disease) in Washington County. Although mumps cases in the United States decreased by 99% after a vaccine was introduced in the 1960s, there has been an increase in mumps cases over the past several years. Residents in the five county district are encouraged to make sure they are current on immunizations. The mumps vaccine (MMR) also protects against measles and rubella. More information can be found at swuhealth.org

Please submit application, resume, and letters of recommendation, to Principal Brandon Jensen at Valley Elementary, 110 East State Street, Orderville, UT. Applications available online at www.kane.k12.ut.us Closing date January 18, 2019, or until filled.

Advertisement for Bid

Kane County School District is accepting bids from qualified, licensed contractors for construction of a restroom/concession/storage building at the Kanab Middle School softball facility. This facility will be approximately 780 square feet and will be cinder block construction. Contractors desiring to bid on this project, please contact Quade Johnson to obtain a bid package. Sealed bids will be received at the Kane County School District Offices, 746 South 175 East, Kanab Utah 84741 (attention Cary Reese) until 3:00 P.M. January 8, 2019. Bids will be opened at 9:00 A.M. on January 9, 2019 at the Kane School District Office. Construction work to commence no later than January 14, 2019 with final completion no later than March 4, 2019. For questions please contact Quade Johnson at johnsonq@kanek12.org. Kane School District reserves the right to reject any or all bids.
